  "critical": false,
  "description": "Solid-state joining via 20-60 kHz mechanical vibration under pressure. Wire bonding: 25μm Au wire at 0.5-2.0W, 20-100ms bond time — dominant IC interconnection method (>10 trillion bonds/year). Thermosonic Au ball bonding (150-250°C) and ultrasonic Al wedge bonding (room temperature). Also joins thin foils, battery tabs, and dissimilar metals without brittle intermetallics.",
